findings.recommended_fix:
Introduce a procedure for issuing EASA Form 1 for components in storage without Form 1, aligned with AMC2 145.A.50(d). For example:

"Issue of EASA Form 1 for components in storage without Form 1
- For components in storage without an EASA Form 1 or equivalent that are intended for installation, the organisation may issue an EASA Form 1 in accordance with AMC2 145.A.50(d), provided it holds the appropriate rating.
- The procedure includes:
  • identification of the component and verification of its configuration;
  • review of available history (logbooks, labels, shipping documents, previous maintenance records);
  • inspection and/or testing as necessary to establish serviceability and eligibility;
  • assessment of any previous abnormal occurrences (accident, incident, heavy landing, lightning strike, etc.);
  • completion of EASA Form 1 with ‘Inspected/Tested’ in block 11 and detailed information in block 12 (last maintenance, manufacturer, date of manufacture, references to original documentation).
- The detailed steps and responsibilities are described in section [x.x.x] of this MOE."
